        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your <strong>giant couscous</strong> and <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong> with your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>sultanas</strong> and 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[600ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[800ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>and cook, covered, for 12-14 min or until all the water has absorbed and the giant couscous is tender</p><p>Wash your<strong> spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once tender,<strong> </strong>stir through the <strong>spinach </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the spinach has wilted– this is your <strong>curried giant couscous</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
